![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a52b1779-e8ca-48ff-aca0-a645bc9028d5/335.jpg?format=original)

Crisis on Infinite Earths is not only a historic and seminal work in DC's comic history, managing the extraordinary task of "fixing" DC's Multiverse problems, but it has been adapted in many forms. The story on it's own has been said to be impenetrable for new readers but how does it fair in animation? Join us as we review the second part of this 3 part adaption of Crisis on Infinite Earths!

Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us wherever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  

